[normal]We do not expect that inserting a provision that the Legal Aid Agency
[normal] (LAA)
[normal] may exceptionally pay costs will improve the situation because the relationship between providers and the 
[normal]LAA
[normal] is such that providers would not treat the possibility of payment as very different to the original proposal of no payment unless permission is g
[normal]ranted. 
[normal]10
[normal]. 
[normal]There are many examples where practitioners have acted to the absolute best of their ability to comply with contractual and other requirements
[normal],
[normal] but the LAA has 
[normal]disagreed with the provider’s interpretation, either:
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]&#xa0;
